---
import DefaultLayout from '@layouts/DefaultLayout.astro'
import { Link } from 'accessible-astro-components'
---

<DefaultLayout title="Experience: Alephium - Ilias">
  <section class="hero my-24">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-8">
        <Link href="/experience" class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider font-bold">← Back to Experience</Link>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold">Alephium - Responsibilities Overview</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
          Senior Software Engineer & Frontend Lead, Core Team · Nov 2021 – Present
        </p>
        <div class="text-lg space-y-4">
          <p>
            My journey with Alephium started in early 2021 in an unexpected way. I had discovered the project through Polto, who had met Alephium's founder, Cheng, at a conference. Curious, I joined their Telegram group. Not long after, Cheng reached out to me directly. They were looking for someone to help rebuild their marketing website, and I offered my consulting services to help them get it off the ground.
          </p>
          <p>
            The team liked my work and the collaboration was so smooth that what started as a freelance gig quickly turned into a permanent position on the core team.
          </p>
          <p>
            Since then, my role has grown tremendously. I am now the core maintainer and frontend lead for Alephium's entire user-facing surface. This means I own the full frontend experience that users touch: I co-built the React Native <a href="/portfolio/alephium-mobile-wallet/">mobile wallet</a> from scratch and took over as core maintainer of the Electron <a href="/portfolio/alephium-desktop-wallet/">desktop wallet</a> and the blockchain explorer.
          </p>
          <p>
            Across these platforms, I architected a Turborepo monorepo with shared SDKs and UI that cut cross-platform delivery time by ~40%. I also drove a complete state-management evolution, and resolved deep performance bottlenecks (making the desktop wallet's cold start 26× faster).
          </p>
          <p>
            Because we are building self-custody wallets for an open-source layer-1 blockchain, security is a first-class part of my remit. I <a href="/blog/clearing-secrets-from-memory/">hardened in-memory secret handling</a>, own the authentication flows (biometrics, fund passwords), encrypted storage, code signing, and supply-chain hygiene - maintaining 0 critical security incidents as we scaled to a peak of 20'000+ monthly active users.
          </p>
          <p>
            Beyond the core wallets, I also rebuilt the token bridge UI (extracting it into a public React widget) and led the frontend of the PowFi DeFi platform. I manage all CI/CD, release lifecycles, and the localization pipeline across every app, while mentoring my teammates and reviewing code across the ecosystem.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="my-24">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="mb-8 text-3xl font-bold border-b pb-4">Key Impact & Achievements</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-4 text-lg">
        <li><strong>Co-built and core maintainer of</strong> Alephium's React Native mobile wallet (App Store + Google Play, 48 production releases) and inherited + own the Electron desktop wallet and blockchain explorer - the ecosystem's primary user touchpoints.</li>
        <li><strong>Architected a Turborepo monorepo</strong> with shared SDKs and UI across web, desktop & mobile - ~40% faster cross-platform delivery at ~80% logic parity.</li>
        <li><strong>Maintained 0 critical security incidents</strong> at a peak of 20'000+ MAU; hardened in-memory secret handling and patched an upstream BIP39 library to close a plaintext recovery-phrase leak.</li>
        <li><strong>Resolved deep performance bottlenecks</strong> in the desktop wallet - 26× faster cold start, 10× overall performance.</li>
        <li><strong>Drove a full state-management evolution</strong> (React state → Redux Toolkit → TanStack Query) backed by competitor analysis (MetaMask, Rainbow, Ledger, Uniswap) and decision docs.</li>
        <li><strong>Rebuilt Alephium's token-bridge UI</strong> (Next.js) and extracted it into a publicly published, reusable React widget consumed across products.</li>
        <li><strong>Led the frontend of the PowFi DeFi platform</strong> - directing a cross-team roadmap and integrating CLMM DEX + staking protocols.</li>
        <li><strong>Own end-to-end CI/CD & release:</strong> EAS → TestFlight/Play Console, signed multi-platform desktop releases, and the Crowdin i18n pipeline across every app.</li>
        <li><strong>Integrated Ledger hardware-wallet support</strong> and secure on-chain transaction flows; own biometrics, encrypted storage, and code signing.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="my-24 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900 py-16">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="mb-12 text-3xl font-bold border-b pb-4">1 &middot; Ownership Map</h2>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-primary">Products I own</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider">DRI for the codebase, end-to-end</p>
          <ul class="space-y-5">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-green-500"></span>
              <div class="flex flex-col">
                <strong class="leading-tight text-lg">Mobile wallet (React Native / Expo)</strong>
                <span class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Owner & Core Maintainer</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-green-500"></span>
              <div class="flex flex-col">
                <strong class="leading-tight text-lg">Desktop wallet (Electron)</strong>
                <span class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Owner & Core Maintainer</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-green-500"></span>
              <div class="flex flex-col">
                <strong class="leading-tight text-lg">Explorer (React)</strong>
                <span class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Owner & Core Maintainer</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-blue-500"></span>
              <div class="flex flex-col">
                <strong class="leading-tight text-lg">alephium.org website</strong>
                <span class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Owner & Core Maintainer</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-blue-500"></span>
              <div class="flex flex-col">
                <strong class="leading-tight text-lg">Bridge UI + published React widget</strong>
                <span class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Owner & Core Maintainer</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-blue-500"></span>
              <div class="flex flex-col">
                <strong class="leading-tight text-lg">PowFi frontend (Next.js)</strong>
                <span class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Owner & Core Maintainer</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-purple-500"></span>
              <div class="flex flex-col">
                <strong class="leading-tight text-lg">Frontend monorepo + shared packages</strong>
                <span class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Owner & Core Maintainer</span>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-primary">Role & Leadership</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider">How I operate</p>
          <ul class="space-y-5">
            <li class="flex flex-col">
              <strong class="leading-tight text-lg mb-1">Frontend lead</strong>
              <span class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Direct the frontend effort; mentor the team's other contributors; review code across the wallets, PowFi SDK/frontend, and @alephium/web3</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex flex-col">
              <strong class="leading-tight text-lg mb-1">Cross-team frontend liaison</strong>
              <span class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Backend, blockchain/protocol, design, marketing</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-primary">Domains I own</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider">The go-to across every product</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Security & Auth</h4>
            <p class="text-sm">Secrets handling, encrypted storage, in-memory secret hygiene, audits, supply-chain. Biometrics, fund password, auth-flow design.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Releases & CI/CD</h4>
            <p class="text-sm">Code signing, EAS → TestFlight/Play Console, signed desktop releases, explorer deploy CI.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Architecture & Performance</h4>
            <p class="text-sm">State management, caching, data-fetching, persistence. The person who profiles and fixes performance issues.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Quality & Standards</h4>
            <p class="text-sm">Testing infra, lint/CI gates, PR conventions. Open-source stewardship (issue triage + community PRs).</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Integrations & Data</h4>
            <p class="text-sm">Internal/External SDKs (WalletConnect, Ledger). Analytics (PostHog/Fathom) + error tracking (Sentry).</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Product Operations</h4>
            <p class="text-sm">Frontend technical roadmap, release planning. Localization (i18n Crowdin pipeline). Production incident response.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="my-24">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="mb-8 text-3xl font-bold border-b pb-4">2 &middot; Initiatives & Impact</h2>
      <p class="mb-8 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Bounded projects I led.</p>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="md:w-1/4 pt-1"><span class="px-3 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 dark:bg-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Mobile Wallet</span></div>
          <div class="md:w-3/4">
            <p><strong>Built & launched the mobile wallet</strong> - co-built it; shipped to the App Store + Google Play on 31 Oct 2023; 48 production releases since.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="md:w-1/4 pt-1"><span class="px-3 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 dark:bg-purple-900 dark:text-purple-100 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Architecture</span></div>
          <div class="md:w-3/4">
            <p><strong>Consolidated the apps into a monorepo</strong> - pnpm + Turborepo; extracted shared logic into internal packages → ~40% faster cross-platform delivery at ~80% logic parity.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="md:w-1/4 pt-1"><span class="px-3 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 dark:bg-purple-900 dark:text-purple-100 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Architecture</span></div>
          <div class="md:w-3/4">
            <p><strong>Re-architected async state twice</strong> - React state → Redux Toolkit → TanStack Query (+ SWR on PowFi), backed by competitor analysis (MetaMask, Rainbow, Ledger, Uniswap) → decision docs.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="md:w-1/4 pt-1"><span class="px-3 py-1 bg-orange-100 text-orange-800 dark:bg-orange-900 dark:text-orange-100 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Performance</span></div>
          <div class="md:w-3/4">
            <p><strong>Performance program</strong> - desktop wallet 26× faster cold start, 10× overall; React Native cold-start; frontend↔backend request-reduction.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="md:w-1/4 pt-1"><span class="px-3 py-1 bg-red-100 text-red-800 dark:bg-red-900 dark:text-red-100 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Security</span></div>
          <div class="md:w-3/4">
            <p><strong>Hardened in-memory secret handling</strong> - moved mnemonics/keys into a wipeable keyring and patched an upstream BIP39 library to close a plaintext recovery-phrase leak found via runtime memory inspection. 0 critical incidents.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="md:w-1/4 pt-1"><span class="px-3 py-1 bg-red-100 text-red-800 dark:bg-red-900 dark:text-red-100 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Security</span></div>
          <div class="md:w-3/4">
            <p><strong>Designed the mobile auth flows</strong> - researched result- vs event-based approaches, competitor analysis, decision docs, then implemented (biometrics + fund password).</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="md:w-1/4 pt-1"><span class="px-3 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 dark:bg-green-900 dark:text-green-100 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Products</span></div>
          <div class="md:w-3/4">
            <p><strong>Rebuilt the token-bridge UI (Next.js)</strong> and extracted it into a publicly published, reusable React widget (consumed by the Bridge UI + PowFi, open for public use).</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="md:w-1/4 pt-1"><span class="px-3 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 dark:bg-green-900 dark:text-green-100 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Products</span></div>
          <div class="md:w-3/4">
            <p><strong>Led the PowFi DeFi frontend</strong> - rewrote it from an open-source codebase to Alephium brand & UX (Next.js); SWR; CLMM DEX + staking integration; directed a cross-team roadmap and liaised with marketing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="md:w-1/4 pt-1"><span class="px-3 py-1 bg-teal-100 text-teal-800 dark:bg-teal-900 dark:text-teal-100 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Ecosystem</span></div>
          <div class="md:w-3/4">
            <p><strong>Migrated @alephium/sdk to ESM</strong> - code splitting, tree shaking, dual export, <a href="/blog/shrinking-alephium-web3-sdk">shrinking the web3 SDK by 88%</a>; also contributed to the core @alephium/web3 SDK.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="md:w-1/4 pt-1"><span class="px-3 py-1 bg-teal-100 text-teal-800 dark:bg-teal-900 dark:text-teal-100 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Ecosystem</span></div>
          <div class="md:w-3/4">
            <p><strong>Integrated the shared PowFi SDK across products</strong> - wired it into both the PowFi app and the mobile wallet (staking); contributed cleanup.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="md:w-1/4 pt-1"><span class="px-3 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 dark:bg-green-900 dark:text-green-100 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Products</span></div>
          <div class="md:w-3/4">
            <p><strong>Built alephium.org</strong> - Figma → responsive, accessible, Web-Vitals-optimized; integrated a git-backed CMS so non-technical editors can publish; migrated the blog off Medium.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 items-start">
          <div class="md:w-1/4 pt-1"><span class="px-3 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 dark:bg-purple-900 dark:text-purple-100 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Architecture</span></div>
          <div class="md:w-3/4">
            <p><strong>Shepherded recurring major framework upgrades</strong> - React 19 + React Compiler, Expo / React Native SDK majors, Electron majors.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="my-24">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="mb-12 text-3xl font-bold border-b pb-4">3 &middot; Capabilities Delivered</h2>
      <p class="mb-8 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">The feature catalog.</p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-10">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">📱 Mobile Wallet</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <li>Secure wallet creation/recovery</li>
            <li>Biometrics (Face ID / fingerprint) & fund password</li>
            <li>Watch-only wallets</li>
            <li>In-app dApp browser bridge (injected-JS WebView↔RN messaging)</li>
            <li>WalletConnect & NFTs</li>
            <li>Address discovery & groups</li>
            <li>Scanning animated QR codes for import</li>
            <li>Fiat on-ramp (Banxa, Onramper)</li>
            <li>Staking (via PowFi SDK)</li>
            <li>Anti-exfiltration hardening (screen-capture prevention, auto-lock, background blur)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">💻 Desktop Wallet</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <li>Ledger hardware-wallet support</li>
            <li>Secure on-chain transaction flows</li>
            <li>Secure wallet export via animated QR code</li>
            <li>WalletConnect & NFTs</li>
            <li>Auto-update (electron-updater)</li>
            <li>alephium:// deep-link handler</li>
            <li>Code signing (Windows + macOS)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="md:col-span-2">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">🌐 Cross-App</h3>
          <ul class="columns-1 md:columns-2 gap-x-8 space-y-2 list-disc ml-5 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 [&>li]:break-inside-avoid">
            <li>Encrypted storage & secrets management</li>
            <li>Error-report sanitization</li>
            <li>Persistence architecture (MMKV / AsyncStorage, React Query cache + storage migrations)</li>
            <li>Real-time data polling</li>
            <li>Analytics (PostHog + Fathom) & Error tracking (Sentry)</li>
            <li>Testing infra (Vitest / Jest / MSW, Testing Library, coverage gates)</li>
            <li>i18n / Crowdin pipeline & Accessibility</li>
            <li>CI/CD pipelines (GitHub Actions; Windows / Ubuntu / macOS matrix)</li>
            <li>Versioning & releases (changesets)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</DefaultLayout>
